title.narrative: CAPACITY DEVELOPMENT IN Communication for Development (C4D)

description.narrative: By the end of 2014, the capacity of partners for developing strategic communication plans is improved to promote and encourage the demand for services (with: MINSA/INLS, MED, MINJUS, MINARS, INAC)., which contributes to Access To Justice, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2014, children, families and duty bearers have the necessary information to change behaviours and make decisions to improve equity and investment in Angola's most vulnerable children.
